This chowder has become an annual New Years tradition for me since I first saw it on the cover of Bon Appetite in 2003. It is a bit labor intensive but worth it, and don't skimp on getting anything but the best ingredients, such as fresh Dungeness crab (I'm on the Pacific coast) and the chanterelle mushrooms. The flavors just melt in your mouth and it is a satisfying meal in itself. Great with fresh warm sourdough bread and Sauvignon Blanc

