A dish everyone should try once. It was too labor intensive for me to want to make again and tweak my mistakes. However, next time I would use canned sweet corn (the corn on the cob I bought wasn't quite in season yet) because I think the recipe needed the corn to be sweet. I omitted the celery (wasn't on hand) and the fennel seeds (ick - fennel!) and substituted some red wine I had around for the sherry; also I used dried thyme. I really liked the chanterelles - I know people have used other mushroom varieties instead, but I'd never tried chanterelles before and I liked what they added to the recipe, even though mine were dried. Overall, a good taste, lots of flavors competing for attention (except the bacon - where did it go?), though I agree with another reviewer that it needed to be thicker - more "chowder-like". Also, one of the priciest recipes I've ever made!

