Rating: 4
Wow. Quite possibly the best soup I have ever made, although I did make several substitutions and modifications. I couldn't find chanterelles, so I substituted them with crimini mushrooms. I'm not a fan of leeks or fennel seeds, so I used carrots instead and omitted the fennel altogether. Didn't feel like having corn that night, so I left that out too. I added a can of clams (juice and all) to add more of a seafood flavor to the broth. I also didn't portion the crab and bacon out like the recipe said--just threw them into the chowder during the last 3 minutes and let them simmer. The flavor and texture were amazingly good. I was kind of afraid the bacon and clams might overpower the flavor, but this was definitely crab chowder. Next time I make this, I'll try it with the corn and chanterelles (if I can find them!).

